4	 * Covers all feat-db-schema acceptance criteria:
5	 *   AC-1  All seven tables exist; PRAGMA table_info returns exact columns.
6	 *   AC-2  FK constraints enforced (nonexistent workflow_id raises FK error).
7	 *   AC-3  ON DELETE CASCADE propagates workflow deletion to all children.
8	 *   AC-4  Partial index idx_pending_attention_open present and used by EXPLAIN.
9	 *   AC-5  Column types are exactly TEXT or INTEGER — no VARCHAR anywhere.
10	 *   AC-6  No columns beyond what sqlite-schema.sql specifies.
11	 *
12	 * Also covers review criteria:
13	 *   RC-1  Partial index WHERE acknowledged_at IS NULL.
14	 *   RC-2  items.data is TEXT (opaque blob), not split columns.
15	 *   RC-3  prepost_runs.when_phase CHECK (pre|post) enforced.
16	 *   RC-4  sessions.parent_session_id FK references sessions(id).
17	 */
